      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Float charge mode is the standard operation mode for the rectifier
modules. The output voltage depends on the float charge settings.
The rectifier modules supply the DC output and charge the battery.
In case the mains input supply is unavailable, the battery supplies
the DC output.</p>
